+## Required Values
+
+Passing `required=True` makes an option mandatory; Click reports an error if it
+is missing. Required options are flagged with a leading `[required]` marker in
+the help output. The marker comes first so that, when a command has several
+options, the markers line up in a single column and the required ones can be
+spotted at a glance.
+
+```{eval-rst}
+.. click:example::
+
+    @click.command()
+    @click.option('--name', required=True, help='The person to greet.')
+    @click.option('--count', default=1, help='Number of greetings.')
+    def hello(name, count):
+        for _ in range(count):
+            click.echo(f'Hello {name}!')
+
+.. click:run::
+
+    invoke(hello, args=['--help'])
+
+```
+
